    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Flywheel and Flywheel Housing -
        Installation - Checking Flywheel Surface Runout
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Checking Flywheel Surface Runout</title>
        <figure id="f2651331" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figH06/H06015.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Checking flywheel surface runout</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Attach a dial indicator to the face of the flywheel housing. Place the tip of the dial
                indicator against the face of the flywheel.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Zero the dial indicator.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slowly rotate the flywheel. Record the total indicator variation and compare the result to
                the flywheel surface runout specification.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
